```java
// Zerodha job queue: process tasks in order received
// Task A arrives at 9:00 → processed first
// Task B arrives at 9:01 → processed second
// FIFO: First In, First Out

// Java: ArrayDeque as queue
Deque<String> queue = new ArrayDeque<>();
queue.offer("Task A");  // enqueue — O(1)
queue.offer("Task B");
queue.offer("Task C");
queue.poll();  // "Task A" — O(1) — FIFO!
queue.peek();  // "Task B" — doesn't remove
```

concept_explanation.queue_java:
**Java Queue: offer/poll (preferred) vs add/remove:**

```java
// As queue (FIFO): use offer at tail, poll from head
Deque<Integer> q = new ArrayDeque<>();
q.offer(1);   // enqueue tail — addLast — O(1)
q.offer(2);
q.offer(3);
q.poll();     // dequeue head — removeFirst — O(1) → 1
q.peek();     // peek head — peekFirst — O(1) → 2

// LinkedList also implements Queue — but ArrayDeque is faster
// offer vs add: offer returns false on capacity limit; add throws exception
// poll vs remove: poll returns null if empty; remove throws NoSuchElementException
// ALWAYS use offer/poll in interviews — safe and idiomatic

